      <h1 class="title-headings fade-in">Total Addressable Market</h1>
      <h2 class="title-subheading fade-in" >Number of Clients Times the Client  </h2>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12 contact-side align-items-center text-center fade-in">
            <p class="contact-para">Total Addressable Market or Total Accessible Market is an estimate of the revenue opportunity derived from 
                your product. It displays the <span class="color-highlight-light">total market demand</span> for your product while <span class="color-highlight-light">highlighting</span>
                 a metric of the underlying potential of 
                the service.<br>
                Broken through scrutiny, TAM comes down to three questions you would want answered while planning your product :<br> <br>
                How many people would <span class="color-highlight-light">want</span> it<br>
                How many people <span class="color-highlight-light">‘can’</span> buy it?<br>
                How <span class="color-highlight-light">large</span> is the market if all of them bought it?<br> <br>
                When competition and distribution challenges are added to the mix, TAM gets reduced to SAM, Serviceable Available Market, 
                calculated through top-bottom, bottom-top and value theory approaches. </p>
        </div>
        <span class="color-highlight-light"> </span>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <h2 class="title-subheading fade-in">Benefits of Quantifying your Product’s Potential</h2>

